    "biography": "<p>Vile dog-sized scorpion-beetle hybrids found in deserts and sandy arratus, dunecrawlers spend most of their life cycle in nests of 3d6 insects, subsisting on solar energy and prey they can hunt individually or in groups of 1d6. Every so often, however, all the dunecrawlers in an area will form a massive swarm that sweeps over all in its path until it collapses in a welter of mating cannibalism, the survivors scattering to form their own nests.</p>"
